BURLEE DRY DOCK CO. v. MORRIS & CUMMINGS DREDGING CO. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 5, 1907.) No. 169. Appeal from tbe District Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York.- Martin A. Ryan, for appellant. Albert A. Wray, for appellee.

Before WALLACE, LACOMBE, and COXE, Circuit Judges.

PER GURIÁM.

Decree (145 Fed. 740) affirmed, with costs.
